node.text:
Lunch box? Check ✔️
Juice box? Check ✔️
Banana? Check ✔️
Massive PB&J Sandwich? Check ✔️
Cake? CHECK 😁👌🏽

It might be a little early to start packing school lunch boxes but it's never too soon to seek out cakespiration! 

Hands up if you'd try making one of these cakes to celebrate back to school with your kids 🙋🏽‍♀️ .

node.text:
As some of you might have guessed by now, I really really love cake 😏. While I typically use fondant in a lot of mine, most of our online Bake You Happy Tutorials don't, which is why I wanted to show off some of these gorgeous cakes from our talented artists 🙌🏽. We've got a decadent S'mores Cake, dreamy Boho Macrame cake and stunning Sculpted Buttercream Sheet Cake with NO fondant required! 
If you'd like to sign up for any of these caketastic classes head to my link in bio!

node.text: I think it goes without saying but when it comes to cake I'm definitely in the camp of "the bigger the better"😋. That's why I'm always caking up giant versions of things! Here are a few of my favorite jumbo cakes that I've made over the years (minus the disastrous McDonalds Apple Pie Cake maybe, because if you know you know 🤬)

node.text:
Soo who else is still drooling at the thought of my peanut butter cake? 🤤You guys have to try it out - it's a game-changer for all those peanut butter lovers out there (I def recommend trying it with chocolate chips)!

You can find this recipe along with tons more in my FREE Basics of Baking Course which I created to help give you the building blocks for creating beautiful cakes. 

Link here 👉 https://bit.ly/basicsofbaking or head to my bio 😊

node.text:
I looove a good juicy slice of watermelon in the summer (who doesn't) but sometimes it's fun to cake up a version too! This Watermelon Cake uses a combination of my Pink Velvet Cake, Italian Meringue Buttercream and plenty of semi-sweet chocolate chips. You won't be spitting out the seeds when it comes to this fruit 😉

Here's the link for the full recipe http://bit.ly/WaterMelonCakeRecipe

node.text:
Officially changing our name to How To Mix It 😂 
It’s always a party when @caspar.haydar and I get together but this time especially since it involved making cocktails with the Bakebook Club members 🙌🏽 As you can see we may have gotten a little sidetracked at times but that’s what happens when you put two Beyoncé’s in the kitchen I guess 🤷🏽‍♀️
Ps. My book club is more than just getting a cute recipe book every month. We love to entertain! Join live streams with the authors and ask them anything or hey there may be another cocktail night with this stud (second to Mr. Cake of course 😉).

node.text:
I can't believe we're already halfway through summer! 😧 
I guess that just means I need to make the most of it while I still can 😎 Check out all these warm weather cakes, perfect for spending a day at the beach. 
The Beach Bag Cake is one of my favorites because I made it for a fellow Torontonian @laurdiy who couldn't believe it was really cake. Sorry Lauren you'll have to put your towel and sunglasses somewhere else, this bag is just for snacking 😉

node.text:
It was my birthday yesterday! I celebrated in the best way by caking up a storm because birthdays are really just natures way of telling us to eat more cake, right? 

Check out some of the birthday gifts I've caked up for myself over the years 👀 Any of them catch your eye?

PSST did you see everything on the HowToCakeIt website is on sale for up to 40% until the 28th! 

Now everyone can enjoy a bit of birthday fun 😉

node.text:
Back to school snacks but let's give them the HTCI treatment shall we? 😏
Now I just need to figure out how I can fit this giant Hostess Cupcake and Twinkie into a lunchbox...

Most of you are aware of my slight obsession with Cake Tees but who remembers the time that I decided to combine my love of cake apparel with the sweet treat itself! Of course I had to use the opportunity to make a couple of stacked t-shirts because you can never have too many options when it comes to cake and clothing 👕. I can't believe this was 6 years ago, time really does fly when you're caking away. Who's been around since this cake??

Lunch box? Check ✔️
Juice box? Check ✔️
Banana? Check ✔️
Massive PB&J Sandwich? Check ✔️

It might be a little early to start packing school lunch boxes but it's never too soon to seek out cakespiration! 

Hands up if you'd try making one of these cakes to celebrate back to school with your kids 🙋🏽‍♀️ .

node.text:
And to think, this moment might not have even been captured had I not reminded Orhan to remove the lens cap from the camera 🤦🏽‍♀️. 
My Honey Cinnamon Buttercream deserves a spotlight moment though, it's so good and super easy to make. Just combine some of your IMBC with honey and a dash of cinnamon and stir it all together. You can use as much honey and cinnamon as you'd like until your satisfied with the flavoring 😋.

node.text:
Excuse me while I reminisce (and drool) over these Back to School Mini Cakes I made STUFFED with Cosmic Brownies, Whipits, Ah Caramel, Passion Flakies and Honeybuns! 🤤 
My favorite part of lunchtime at school used to be opening up my lunchbox to see what treat my mom had packed me. I decided to cake all five of my all-time favorite school lunch treats because no one should have to choose, or share 😉.

node.text:
As some of you might have guessed by now, I really really love cake 😏. While I typically use fondant in a lot of mine, most of our online Bake You Happy Tutorials don't, which is why I wanted to show off some of these gorgeous cakes from our talented artists 🙌🏽. We've got a decadent S'mores Cake, dreamy Boho Macrame cake and stunning Sculpted Buttercream Sheet Cake with NO fondant required! 
If you'd like to sign up for any of these caketastic classes head to my link in bio!

node.text:
Who lives in a pineapple under my stand mixer?? Spongebob Squarepants of course! Or at least the caked up version of him 🤫 
The man, the myth, the legend from Bikini Bottom was too famous not to make an appearance on How to Cake It so I decided to cake him with a combination of my trusty vanilla AND chocolate cake along with plenty of Chocolate Swiss Meringue Buttercream between the layers 🧽. 
I'm ready, I'm ready! 🙋🏽‍♀️

node.text: I think it goes without saying but when it comes to cake I'm definitely in the camp of "the bigger the better"😋. That's why I'm always caking up giant versions of things! Here are a few of my favorite jumbo cakes that I've made over the years (minus the disastrous McDonalds Apple Pie Cake maybe, because if you know you know 🤬)
